quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  7,148,"And the people of Moses, after he had left them, chose (for worship) an image of a lowing calf (or one that seemed to low) made out of their ornaments. Did they not see that it could not speak to them or guide them in the path? They chose it and became wr"
  7,149,"But when they bit their hands (in realization and fear) and saw that they had gone astray, they said, \"Verily, if our Lord have not compassion on us and forgive us we shall surely be of those who are lost"
  7,150,"And when Moses returned unto his people angry and grieved, he said, \"Evil is it that which you have done after I had gone! Would you hasten on the judgment of your Lord?\". And he threw down the tablets and seized his brother by the (hair on his)"
  7,151,"Moses prayed, \"O Lord! Forgive my brother and me and let us enter into Thy mercy; for Thou art the most merciful of the merciful"